# Project Rules

## Architecture
- Frontend follows Feature Slice Design (FSD)
- Pages live inside their feature folder e.g. features/boards/pages/
- Each feature exposes a public boundary via index.js
- No direct imports from deep feature paths outside the feature

## Frontend
- Use MUI components only, no plain HTML elements for UI
- useEffect and useState live in hooks, not components
- Services are transport only, no business logic
- Hooks own the decision of what to extract from responses

## Backend
- Controllers are entry points only, no business logic
- Business logic lives in the service layer
- Services communicate via interfaces for DI

## General
- pnpm for package management
- Biome for linting and formatting
- C# backend, React frontend

Do not provide me answers.
I want to be lead to a solution, make me think of the solution.
Suggestion should have structure that allows me to learn and use the learned concepts/techniques etc and apply them in the upcoming implementation.
Before moving on always ask for review of the solution and possible ways to optimise.
